Superstition Wilderness Hiking

Kim’s Mom has a place near Superstition Mountain which we try to visit annually. In 2022 I started mapping hikes that we made in the Superstition Wilderness. Those hikes are shown below. More information on some specific walks is in the next section.

Interactions with Map

  • red are roads, orange are trails numbered by the Forest Service, gold are named (but not numbered) trails, and brown are unnamed (nor numbered) trails.
  • Hover on track to see track abbreviation.
  • Click on track to get track information.
  • Use +/- in upper-left to zoom.
  • Use object in upper-right to change base map type.
  • Use object in lower-left to make measurements on map.

 

Specific Hikes

Specific hikes that we have enjoyed are highlighted below.

  • 2025
    • Praying Hands (from First Water Rd)
    • Siphon Draw (from E Singletree Rd)
    • Superstition Ridgeline (Hieroglyphics TH to Siphon Draw Tr)
    • Jacob’s Crosscut (Broadway TH to E Singletree Rd)
  • 2024
    • Lost Goldmine (Hieroglyphics TH to Carney Springs)
    • Weaver’s Needle Cross Loop
    • Goldmine (Broadway TH to E Cloudview Ave)
    • Robber’s Roost (via Fremont Saddle)
    • Hackberry Springs Loop II
  • 2023
    • Broadway Cave & Monument Canyon Mine Shaft
    • Peralta TH to Canyon Lake Marina
    • Hackbery Springs Loop I
    • Robber’s Roost Loop (Carney Springs to Peralta TH)
  • 2022
    • Wave Cave
    • Hieroglyphics Trail
    • Peralta & Cave Trail Loop
    • Black Top Mesa (from First Waters TH)
    • Massacre Falls
